FOODBORNE ILLNESS - CHINA: (JIANGXI)
************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 18 Sep 2014
Source: Daijiworld, Indo Asian News Service (IANS) [edited]
http://www.daijiworld.com/news/news_disp.asp?n_id=264288


At least 320 people in China have been hospitalized due to suspected food poisoning, health officials said Thu 18 Sep 2014. According to the officials, most of the patients, aged 3 to 18 suffered from diarrhea, nausea, stomach pain, and fever in Jiangxi province, Xinhua reported.

Initial investigations suggest they contracted a bacterial infection from food or water poisoning.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[There is not enough information here to assess etiology but it is stated that a bacterial cause is suggested. Viruses, bacteria, and protozoa all could be causal here. Epidemiologically, there is no information regarding common foods or other potential commonalities of the cases. - Mod.LL

Maps of China can be seen at http://www.sacu.org/maps/provmap.png and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2783743,343. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]
